==Old English==
===Etymology===
From the base of [[midd]] + [[geard|ġeard]].  Often misinterpreted since Old English times as [[midd]] + [[eard]].  Cognate with Old Saxon [[middelgard]], Old High German [[mittangart]], Old Norse [[miðgarðr]], Gothic [[𐌼𐌹𐌳𐌾𐌿𐌽𐌾𐌰𐍂𐌳𐍃]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'mɪddanjæaɹd/

===Noun===
'''middanġeard''' ''m''
# [[middle-earth]], the known [[world]], the [[earth]]

